[2026-03-18T11:24:17.451Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013xL8oMUDFxR974ndLtFVvz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are in place. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`auditLog.ts`** — Added `AuditWriteError` custom error class. Changed `record()` to log at `error` level with the full `entry` payload (not just the action name), then re-throw as `AuditWriteError` instead of silently swallowing the failure.\n\n2. **`auditPolicy.ts`** — Wrapped the `record()` call in event listeners with try-catch. The error is already logged at error level inside `record()`, so the catch just prevents the throw from crashing the emitter's listener chain.\n\n3. **`dispatcher.ts`** — Wrapped both `record()` calls with try-catch so audit failures don't break the decrypt operation flow.\n\n4. **`httpApi.ts`** — Wrapped the `record()` call with try-catch so audit failures don't break credential creation.\n\n**Design rationale:** `record()` now throws `AuditWriteError` so any new caller is forced to handle audit failures explicitly — they can't accidentally swallow them. Existing callers in fire-and-forget contexts catch the error gracefully since `record()` already emits an `error`-level log with the full entry payload, making audit trail gaps detectable via log monitoring/alerting."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":394,"cache_read_input_tokens":38439,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":394},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6243d3f8-5d06-4cc6-80a1-550653b91f4e","uuid":"c53cf481-1610-4d7e-bdd5-693c86c1d16d"}
